Additional System Components include:



1.    Three (3) Oil Pots (one at intercooler and one at each liquid recirculator package) for draining oil)

2.    One (1) Automatic Purger, and

3.    Ammonia Diffusion Tank (all relief valve discharge lines lead to the diffusion tank for mixing with water in the event of a release from a system component PRV).



Primary Safety Systems include:



1.    Dual pressure relief valves on all pressure vessels;

2.    Pressure relief and relief piping system to ammonia diffusion tank;

3.    Compressor control panels to shut down the compressor operation if safe operating conditions are exceeded;

4.    Liquid level float switches and level columns;

5.    High level vessel alarms;

6.    Emergency refrigeration control switches for emergency shutdown of the system (E-Stop);

7.    Ventilation system for continuous and emergency ventilation of the Engine Room and LRP1 Pump Package Room;

8.    Ammonia detection and alarm system for response to elevated levels of ammonia vapor in the Engine Room and freezer area;

9.    Ammonia diffusion tank (all relief valve discharge lines lead to the diffusion tank for mixing with water in the event of a release from a component relief valve);

10.    Fire diffusion panel for use by the fire department in the event of a fire emergency

11.    Manual stop valves;

12.    Manual and solenoid-controlled "King Valve" to stop liquid refrigerant flow from the high-pressure receivers;

13.    Physical barriers to protect equipment/piping from collisions (e.g. bollards);

14.    Fire extinguishers; and

15.    Emergency showers and eyewash stations



The refrigeration system was designed and constructed under the applicable fire and mechanical codes in effect at the time of installation.  See P&ID's for equipment layout.



